<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1050652 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Only-One-Twitter-Peruzzi_Vibes.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Only-One-Twitter-Peruzzi_Vibes.jpg 300w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Only-One-Twitter-Peruzzi_Vibes-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Only-One-Twitter-Peruzzi_Vibes-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Only-One-Twitter-Peruzzi_Vibes-240x240.jpg 240w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> As we await the release of his upcoming album, Nigerian singer Peruzzi has released a new single titled “Only One”. In the Speroach Beatz produced track, the DMW artiste claims to be the only one that his love interest ever loved. “Only One” is a follow up to his previous track “Nana”. About two weeks ago, Peruzzi announced his long-awaited debut album “Huncho Vibes”. The soon to be released album is a follow up to his last body of work “Heartwork” – his debut EP, which was released about a year ago.  Listen to “Only One” below: 